  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Strong spasms of the musculature of the esophagus that can last minutes to hours and mimic the chest pain of angina\nUnclear what causes esophageal spasm. Possibly related to food intolerance.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Squeezing or tightening pain in the chest\nCan have associated\ndysphagia\n+/- globus sensation\nCan be triggered by eating hot or cold drinks/food.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
